[Full text of the objective 11.2 "All programmes and projects funded in partner countries have an ex ante environmental assessment procedure, ranging, as appropriate, from environmental screening to full environmental impact assessment or strategic environmental assessment" from the National Strategy](/objectives/11#subobjective_2)

#### Flanders:

  * Waarschijnlijk hier en daar, maar gebeurt dit ook systematisch? 

#### Federal:

Discussion enc ours entre DGCD - VUB pour developper l'application effective de l'evaluation d'impact environnemental via le developpement d'un toolkit pour faciliter son utilisation.

Future actions:

  * Apply a screening procedure of all Belgium's development cooperation projects prior to the decision to allocate funds and carry out a full Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) when it proves necessary, so that potential negative impacts on the biodiversity of recipient countries can be identified at an early stage and be avoided or mitigated; 
  * Broader strategic approaches, such as "Indicative Cooperation Programmes, "Country Strategic Papers" or "Sector-Wide Approaches" (SWAP), etc., should be subject to a Strategic Environmental Assessment* (SEA) that includes biodiversity considerations; 
  * Both EIAs and SEAs should be performed by using the existing assessment systems of the recipient country as much as possible. Joint EIAs or SEAs by several donors will be encouraged whenever possible; 
  * Ex post evaluations of development cooperation programmes or projects should integrate biodiversity considerations, even in projects/programmes that are not related to natural resources.

[Full text of the objective 5.2 Encourage the involvement of the private sector in the protection of biodiversity, as an integral part of business planning and operations* " from the National Strategy](/objectives/5#subobjective_2)

#### Brussels:

Active promotion to integrate biodiversity is going on: to sectors of architecture, building, companies,...

#### Walloon Region:

Mis a part les partenaires tels que les agriculteurs, les forestiers, les chasseurs et les pecheurs, voici quelques types de projets ou des acteurs du secteurs prive contribuent d'une maniere ou d'une autre a la preservation de la biodiversite:

  * Elia (et avant Electrabel) signe des conventions avec la DNF pour l'entretien ecologique des zones situees sous les lignes electriques;  
  * Electrabel soutien divers projets en Wallonie dont l'Aquascope de Virelles;  
  * Electrabel soutien financierement certaines associations de protection de la nature pour l'acquisition de terrains  
  * Prix Interbrew accorde a des initiatives interessantes au niveau conservation de la nature;   
  * Valvert : Festival du Film Nature et peut-etre d'autres initiatives;  
  * Subsides a des association de conservation de la nature (par ex: Tom & Co, Nature et decouverte, le gaz naturel, banque triodos, et Vivara entre autres sont des partenaires de Natagora);  
  * Certains exploitants de carrieres peuvent prendre des mesures afin de ne pas perturber les nichees d'hirondelles;  
  * Reamenagement des carriere de cimenterie: les plans d'exploitation des carrieres de cimenterie prevoient la rehabilitation des sites. La vocation finale des anciens sites carriers est souvent le retour a la nature.  
  * certaines entreprises privees soignent les abords de leur batiments/infrastructures en tenant compte certains element favorables a la biodiversite 
  * certaines entreprises privees restaurent des zones humides afin de preserver la qualite de l'eau et/ou de sensibiliser leurs employes a l'utilite des zones humides (exemple: GlaxoSmithKline) 
  * ECOSEM sprl est une societe specialisee dans la production de semences et de plantes indigenes d'origine controlee. 

#### Federal:

  * consultation of plant sector with regard to IAS  
  * first study towards belgian users of genetice resources with regard to ABS

#### Future actions:

  * Inform the private sector about the importance of biodiversity, the legislations protecting it and the opportunities to take actions to preserve it; 
  * State aids to private sector operators.

[Full text of the objective 5.3 "Ensure that this Strategy is taken into account in decision-making and policy discussions" from the National Strategy](/objectives/5#subobjective_3)

#### Federal:

diffusion of the NBS to relevant federal stakeholders (FPS, agencies) work of integration of biodiversity in 4 key federal sector in replaced the framework of the NBS

#### Future actions:

  * Consider biodiversity from the early stages of the drafting process when developing new planning levels; 
  * Develop guidelines or checklists to help relevant departments to take biodiversity concern into account when developing legislations, plans or programs in other sectors in order to not damage biodiversity and actively contribute to its conservation and stainable use;   
  * Continually review the adequacy of legislation in furthering the objectives of the Belgian Biodiversity Strategy; 
  * Designate a contact person in each sector in charge of ensuring integration of conservation and sustainable use of biodiversity requirements in the sector.

[Full text of the objective 5.6 "Take biodiversity concern into account in national export credit policy" from the National Strategy](/objectives/5#subobjective_6)

#### Flanders:

Export: federale bevoegdheid

#### Federal:

Ongoing reflection within the framework of the development of action plan 'economy and biodiveristy' , in particular development of a specific action with the Belgian Export Credit Agency

#### Future actions:

  * Project screening procedures must ensure that activities that lead to irreversible damage to biodiversity are not promoted; 
  * Implement a harmonised procedure to check whether a project respond to the international biodiversity related obligations and engagements subscribed by Belgium; 
  * Organise training for credit export agencies staff Belgium's international obligations and engagements related to biodiversity; 
  * Ask companies to sign a declaration of intent setting out the commitments of the companies to meet the objectives of the national biodiversity strategy.

[Full text of the objective 7.7 "Make best use of Belgian expertise to support implementation of the Convention in developing countries" from the National Strategy](/objectives/7#subobjective_7)

#### Flanders:

MR386 Milieu, ontwikkelingssamenwerking en armoedebestrijding integreren en uitbouwen: vanuit milieuoogpunt de Noord-Zuid-samenwerking bevorderen binnen het kader van het Vlaamse ontwikkelingssamenwerkingsbeleid en anderzijds in milieuprojecten in ontwikkelingslanden armoedebestrijding, duurzame consumptie en productie en/of het behoud en duurzaam beheer van natuurlijke rijkdommen centraal stellen. De nadruk zal hierbij liggen op capaciteitsopbouw, met name op samenwerking en uitwisseling van expertise om de nodige structuren, methodologie en een regelgevend kader uit te bouwen. Naast de samenwerking van overheid tot overheid is er ook samenwerking mogelijk met intermediaire en wetenschappelijke organisaties en met maatschappelijke groepen. Voorbeelden hiervan zijn de ondersteuning van lokale overheden en de samenwerking inzake duurzaam landgebruik, duurzaam bosbeheer, afvalpreventie en -recyclage en bestrijding van bodemerosie.

#### Brussels:

Not applicable in the Brussels Capital Region.

#### Future actions:

  * Support capacity-building for identification and monitoring of biodiversity; 
  * Make easier access to biodiversity data stored in Belgian collections, archives and databases; 
  * Promote scientific and technical cooperation; 
  * Transfer relevant technologies to address biodiversity matters; 
  * Develop educational and public awareness programmes.
